tweet: We need to get rid of the mentality that people are ‚Äústuck‚Äù at  home. You are SAFE at home.

tweet: No matter where you live or how old you are, EVERYONE should be staying home as much as possible. By not following these orders, you are putting yourself and everyone around you at risk.

name: Governor Mike Parson
tweet:
As I have said many times, the COVID-19 situation changes EVERY DAY. Every day, we are constantly re-evaluating and looking at all possible options.
 
But again, the most important step anyone can take right now is STAYING HOME.

name: Governor Mike Parson
tweet: These are not easy decisions, but just as families and businesses have to balance their budgets and make hard decisions, we are doing the same. This is the right thing to do to make sure our budget is balanced and we are financially prepared to deal with the impacts of COVID-19.

name: Governor Mike Parson
tweet: Of the $180 million, I assure you these restrictions are absolutely necessary and include funding for several departments ‚Äì many of which are priorities of my own administration. In addition, the Judiciary & Secretary of State have worked to identify savings in their own budgets.

name: Governor Mike Parson
tweet: In addition to the $180 million we‚Äôre restricting in the budget, we are hopeful we may be able to use an additional $315 million dollars in federal funding this year to help with the shortfall.

name: Governor Mike Parson
tweet: To ensure our budget is balanced and we have the funds to combat COVID-19 going forward, we are planning to restrict $180 million dollars in spending.

name: Governor Mike Parson
tweet:
Between now and June 31st, we are estimating an over $500 million shortfall.
 
We have had to take a hard look at our budget and make some very difficult decisions.

name: Governor Mike Parson
tweet: While we still do not know the true impact of COVID-19 on the economy, we do know that we have to act NOW.

name: Governor Mike Parson
tweet: When we began this fiscal year, we anticipated economic growth, and we had based our budget on that growth. COVID-19 has had serious impacts on our anticipated economic growth, and now we are expecting significant revenue declines.

name: Governor Mike Parson
tweet:
However, the impact of COVID-19 has already been hard felt in our economy.
 
More people are staying home. Businesses operations have been limited, many people have lost their jobs, and state revenues are down.

name: Governor Mike Parson
tweet: The General Assembly has also shown great restraint and leadership in passing conservative budgets, and by working together, we have been able to ensure that our state is financially sound.

name: Governor Mike Parson
tweet:
Last year, we were able to leave $100 million dollars on the bottom line in order to respond to any unexpected revenue declines.
 
We also proposed to do the same for next year, ensuring
another year of responsible state budgeting and savings.

name: Governor Mike Parson
tweet:
Up until this point in my administration, we have been very fortunate to have a booming economy with record low unemployment & high wage growth.
 
Incomes have gone up, & taxes have gone down.
We have, at many times, had more jobs available than we have had people to fill them.

name: Governor Mike Parson
tweet: As I said yesterday, COVID-19 is having a serious impact not only on public health, but also our economy.

name: Governor Mike Parson
tweet:
As of 2:00 p.m. today, there have been 1,581 positive cases of COVID-19 in Missouri, including 18 deaths.
 
Approximately 17,500 people have been tested so far in Missouri.

name: Governor Mike Parson
